    <string name="faq_expand_content_description">Expand answer</string>
    <string name="faq_question_scan_modes">What is the difference between automatic and manual mode?</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_scan_modes">In automatic mode, scan feedback closes after a few seconds. In manual mode, it stays visible until you tap Close.</string>
    <string name="faq_question_qr_not_found">What should I do if a QR is not recognized?</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_qr_not_found">Check that you are inside the correct event, that the QR belongs to that event, and that the invitation exists in the guest list.</string>
    <string name="faq_question_seat">Where does the guest seat come from?</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_seat">The seat is read from the guest asiento field in the database. If it does not exist or is empty, Qntrol shows Not assigned.</string>
    <string name="faq_question_manual_check">What is the manual check for?</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_manual_check">It lets you mark an entry without scanning the QR, for example if the guest has an issue with their code.</string>
    <string name="faq_question_logs">What information do logs save?</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_logs">Logs save app access and entries accepted by QR or manual check. They are kept locally for 30 days.</string>
    <string name="faq_question_dark_mode">Does dark mode affect scanning?</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_dark_mode">No. Dark mode only changes the app appearance; scanning and records work the same way.</string>
